# plugin overview

skogai-marketplace
  indexes plugins
  describes capabilities
  maps compatibility
  exposes install/discovery metadata
  does not own plugin internals

skogai-core
  loads enabled plugins
  resolves routing/context
  builds prompt/context bundles
  dispatches actions
  observes triggers
  applies hooks
  records events/diffs

skogai-plugin-*
  owns one capability domain
  provides files/prompts/contracts/actions/hooks

# plugin shape
  identity
  description
  capabilities
  provided context
  provided actions
  provided triggers
  provided hooks
  routing hints
  expected inputs
  expected outputs
  compatibility
  safety constraints
  lifecycle notes

# plugins answer
  what are you?
  what do you provide?
  when should you be loaded?
  who should read you?
  what actions do you expose?
  what events do you listen to?
  what hooks do you participate in?
  what input do you expect?
  what output do you produce?
  what should never happen silently?

