Clean Initial Scope

I would avoid building “the system” at first. Define only the maps.

First pass:

1. Root context file conventions
2. Plugin identity model
3. Marketplace plugin record model
4. Action/trigger/hook vocabulary
5. File plugin as first example plugin

Second pass:

1. Add compatibility/deprecation model
2. Add plugin categories
3. Add context routing rules
4. Add safety levels
5. Add agent/client-specific router files

Third pass:

1. Loader implementation
2. Validation
3. CLI commands
4. Marketplace indexing
5. Plugin install/update flow

Current best target shape:

skogai
  owns runtime and routing

skogai-marketplace
  owns discovery and metadata

skogai-plugin-files
  owns the first extracted skill/capability

every repo
  owns a SKOGAI.md router file

every plugin
  owns PLUGIN.md, ACTIONS.md, TRIGGERS.md, HOOKS.md, CONTEXT.md

every action
  has typed input/output expectations

every trigger
  describes an observed event

every hook
  describes a lifecycle attachment point
